FT  30 APR 93 / International Company News: Ferranti's US assets for sale
FERRANTI, the UK defence electronics company whose former US deputy chairman
is now in prison for fraud and illegal arms sales, is winding up one of its
US companies and seeking buyers for its remaining US assets.
In Ferranti's last financial year, ended on March 31 1992, the US businesses
contributed Pounds 113.9m of total group turnover of Pounds 409m (Dollars
629m).
The US company being wound up is Ferranti International Simulation and
Training.
